Inkaku is the Japanese word for Clitoris. The word Inkaku is composed of the two kanji characters 陰(in) 核(kaku). 陰(in) means the sex organ; secret; shadow, while 核(kaku) means nucleus or core. In slang, the word is Kurichan. Composed of the kanji 栗(kuri) which means chestunt and ちゃん (chan) which is an honorific term given to people, such as sir or madam. However, the term chan is given to people younger than oneself or to someone you have affection for, making kurichan something like "my little chestnut".